                      "collapsed": false,
                      "completed": false,
                      "children": []
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "71e6fe18-848e-4706-be3e-0ad2ab5ffae9",
                      "text": {
                        "ops": [
                          {
                            "insert": "Options: 1) Buy chicken rice again for dinner; 2) Choose a different but similarly easy hawker-style meal; 3) Choose a deliberately healthier, lighter option (e.g., fish soup, salad, home-cooked); 4) Have a light or partial dinner or skip; 5) Adopt a micro-protocol that sets chicken rice as the default with one defined backup and decides in under 2 minutes."
                          },
                          {
                            "insert": "\n",
                            "attributes": {
                              "paragraph": true
                            }
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      "format": {
                        "node": "bullet",
                        "children": "bullet"
                      },
                      "collapsed": false,
                      "completed": false,
                      "children": []
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "45532e5a-e6a9-4f0f-af98-7b5b667ccf34",
                      "text": {
                        "ops": [
                          {
                            "insert": "Decision: Use a simple two-step protocol tonight: (1) quickly check if I still genuinely want chicken rice and have no strong health/budget downside; if yes, buy chicken rice again without guilt; (2) if not, fall back to one pre-chosen, similarly easy hawker-style alternative and commit to it without further debate."
                          },
                          {
                            "insert": "\n",
                            "attributes": {
                              "paragraph": true
                            }
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      "format": {
                        "node": "bullet",
                        "children": "bullet"
                      },
                      "collapsed": false,
                      "completed": false,
                      "children": []
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "89236127-1745-4b23-8322-b1837cd37ce8",
                      "text": {
                        "ops": [
                          {
                            "insert": "Reasoning: Repeating chicken rice once in a day has negligible long-term health impact compared to overall weekly diet, while switching for the sake of variety alone adds decision friction without guaranteed nutritional benefit; a clear default-plus-single-backup rule gives me either full convenience (chicken rice again) or low-effort variety (one defined alternative) and avoids the worst outcome—overthinking, stalling, and feeling conflicted over a trivial decision."
                          },
                          {
                            "insert": "\n",
                            "attributes": {
                              "paragraph": true
                            }
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      "format": {
                        "node": "bullet",
                        "children": "bullet"
